DoublyLinkedList
- purpose: to keep order
- Space complexity: O(n)
- Time complexity:
    insert/delete: O(1)
    indexing: O(n)
    
-LinkedList + HashMap: tracking duplicates, updating
-LinkedList + Queue: mixing in nodes with priority and non-priority
-LinkedList + Stack: tracking specific data

-HashMaps: specific info
    dict, constant access to everything
    - keeping locations addresses of nodes
        - space: O(k)
        - time: O(1) access **the only ds
        
        
-BinarySearchTree:
    - inorder: sorted data
    - Time: O(h); worst case O(n), best case O(logn)
